description: A large group of people stands under a 'WELCOME AMELIA' banner, many looking skyward or into the distance through binoculars, as if awaiting an arrival. One person in the foreground, also holding binoculars, expresses concern about a roast in the oven. The scene contrasts a seemingly significant public event with a mundane, private worry, highlighting the absurdity of conflicting priorities.
caption: “Well, I’m just starting to worry about that roast in the oven, that’s all.”
